WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.125 --> 00:00:04.804
COPD is a chronic obstructive lung disease
that makes it hard to move air

2
00:00:04.805 --> 00:00:08.184
out of the lungs. The key problem is
incomplete exhalation.

3
00:00:08.784 --> 00:00:11.104
When air cannot leave efficiently, it
becomes trapped.

4
00:00:11.604 --> 00:00:13.765
Lung volume increases, the diaphragm
flattens,

5
00:00:13.864 --> 00:00:15.685
and the patient must work harder to
breathe.

6
00:00:16.165 --> 00:00:19.844
COPD usually includes a mix of chronic
bronchitis and emphysema.

7
00:00:20.645 --> 00:00:22.604
Chronic bronchitis is mainly an airway
problem.

8
00:00:23.145 --> 00:00:26.645
Inflammation and excess mucus narrow the
airways, causing chronic productive

9
00:00:26.645 --> 00:00:29.004
cough, coarse breath sounds, wheezing,

10
00:00:29.524 --> 00:00:31.305
secretion retention, and infection risk.

11
00:00:31.805 --> 00:00:33.865
Emphysema is mainly an alveolar problem.

12
00:00:34.564 --> 00:00:37.244
Alveolar walls are destroyed, elastic
recoil is lost,

13
00:00:37.604 --> 00:00:40.185
and small airways collapse more easily
during exhalation.

14
00:00:40.705 --> 00:00:42.944
This leads to air trapping,
hyperinflation,

15
00:00:43.744 --> 00:00:45.784
diminished breath sounds, barrel chest,
and

16
00:00:45.784 --> 00:00:46.724
dyspnea with activity.

17
00:00:47.604 --> 00:00:51.365
Gas exchange worsens because ventilation
and perfusion are not evenly matched.

18
00:00:51.544 --> 00:00:54.485
This VQ mismatch commonly causes
hypoxemia.

19
00:00:55.104 --> 00:00:59.305
Carbon dioxide retention can occur in
advanced disease, acute exacerbation,

20
00:00:59.485 --> 00:01:03.345
or respiratory muscle fatigue, but not
every COPD patient retains

21
00:01:03.345 --> 00:01:04.044
carbon dioxide.

22
00:01:04.584 --> 00:01:07.324
That is why SpO2 alone is not enough.

23
00:01:08.025 --> 00:01:10.665
RTs must assess work of breathing, breath
sounds,

24
00:01:11.364 --> 00:01:13.944
respiratory pattern, mental status, oxygen
requirement,

25
00:01:14.264 --> 00:01:16.084
and ABG or VBG trends.

26
00:01:17.004 --> 00:01:18.864
COPD is confirmed with spirometry.

27
00:01:18.864 --> 00:01:24.565
A reduced post-bronchodilator FEV1 over
FVC supports obstructive airflow limitation.

28
00:01:25.525 --> 00:01:28.205
Gold airflow grades use FEV1% predicted.

29
00:01:28.905 --> 00:01:30.585
GOLD 1 is 80% or higher.

30
00:01:31.285 --> 00:01:33.484
GOLD 2 is 50% to 79%.

31
00:01:33.484 --> 00:01:35.785
GOLD 3 is 30% to 49%.

32
00:01:35.785 --> 00:01:38.085
And GOLD 4 is below 30%.

33
00:01:38.595 --> 00:01:42.205
For board questions, remember that GOLD
describes airflow limitation,

34
00:01:42.385 --> 00:01:47.044
but the patient's current severity also
depends on symptoms, exacerbation

35
00:01:47.044 --> 00:01:49.224
history, oxygenation, ventilation,

36
00:01:49.504 --> 00:01:50.565
and clinical status.

37
00:01:51.404 --> 00:01:54.345
During an exacerbation, watch for
increased dyspnea,

38
00:01:55.065 --> 00:01:57.485
increased cough, thicker or purulent
sputum,

39
00:01:58.144 --> 00:02:00.665
increased oxygen need, worsening air
movement,

40
00:02:01.224 --> 00:02:03.205
fatigue, and poor response to treatment.

41
00:02:03.885 --> 00:02:08.865
Red flags include new confusion or
drowsiness, rising PaCO2 with

42
00:02:08.865 --> 00:02:11.904
falling pH, silent chest, inability to

43
00:02:11.904 --> 00:02:15.085
speak full sentences, severe fatigue,
sudden

44
00:02:15.085 --> 00:02:18.785
unilateral absent breath sounds, or no
improvement after therapy.

45
00:02:20.164 --> 00:02:24.785
Management includes titrated oxygen when
hypoxemic, bronchodilators to reduce airway

46
00:02:24.785 --> 00:02:29.164
resistance, corticosteroids during
exacerbations, antibiotics when

47
00:02:29.164 --> 00:02:32.884
infection is suspected, and airway
clearance for selected patients with

48
00:02:32.884 --> 00:02:33.925
retained secretions.

49
00:02:34.524 --> 00:02:36.884
NIV, such as BiPAP, may be

50
00:02:36.884 --> 00:02:40.244
needed when increased work of breathing,
elevated PaCO2,

51
00:02:40.304 --> 00:02:43.044
and low pH suggest ventilatory failure.

52
00:02:43.845 --> 00:02:46.225
If mental status, acidosis, or distress

53
00:02:46.225 --> 00:02:49.104
worsens despite NIV, escalate urgently.

54
00:02:49.884 --> 00:02:50.625
The big takeaway.

55
00:02:51.404 --> 00:02:55.505
COPD causes obstruction, obstruction
causes incomplete exhalation,

56
00:02:56.225 --> 00:03:00.044
incomplete exhalation causes air trapping,
and air trapping increases work

57
00:03:00.044 --> 00:03:02.005
of breathing and gas exchange problems.

58
00:03:02.404 --> 00:03:05.744
A strong RT asks, is this patient
oxygenating,

59
00:03:06.225 --> 00:03:08.904
ventilating, moving air, clearing
secretions,

60
00:03:09.744 --> 00:03:12.625
responding to therapy, and maintaining the
strength to keep breathing?

